    <p>Cortisol is a glucocorticoid steroid hormone synthesized in the zona fasciculata of the adrenal cortex. In evolutionary terms, cortisol was designed for survival — it mobilizes glucose, suppresses non-essential functions (digestion, reproduction, immune response), and sharpens cognitive focus during acute threats. The problem in 2026 is that the threats are no longer acute. Work deadlines, financial pressure, social media comparison, poor sleep, and processed food keep cortisol chronically elevated, converting a life-saving hormone into a slow-acting metabolic poison.</p>

